---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout 
  title="Product - Entitle" 
  description="Feature Enablement as a Service - Externalize commercial access policy from your SaaS application"
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="product-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="product-hero-content">
        <span class="badge">Feature Enablement as a Service</span>
        <h1>Policy Decision Platform<br/>for Modern B2B SaaS</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Entitle externalizes commercial access policy from your codebase. We evaluate <strong>whether</strong> 
          capability access is allowed‚Äîyou enforce <strong>what happens next</strong>.
        </p>
        <div class="cta-buttons">
          <a href={`${base}alpha`} class="btn btn-primary">Request Alpha Access</a>
          <a href={`${base}docs`} class="btn btn-secondary">Read Documentation</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Core Value Proposition -->
  <section class="core-value">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="value-statement">
        <h2>We externalize commercial access policy ‚Äî not your business logic.</h2>
        <p>That principle defines the product, the architecture, and the value proposition.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Entitle Delivers -->
  <section class="what-delivers">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="badge badge-primary">Platform Capabilities</span>
        <h2>What the Platform Delivers</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="delivery-categories">
        <div class="category">
          <div class="category-header">
            <div class="category-icon">üéØ</div>
            <h3>Decision Engine</h3>
          </div>
          <ul>
            <li>Feature and capability entitlements</li>
            <li>Plan-to-capability mappings</li>
            <li>Trials, grace periods, and expirations</li>
            <li>Usage limits and quota signals</li>
            <li>Rollouts and kill switches</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="category">
          <div class="category-header">
            <div class="category-icon">üîå</div>
            <h3>Runtime & Integration</h3>
          </div>
          <ul>
            <li>Low-latency decision API (P95 &lt; 10ms target)</li>
            <li>Entitlement snapshots for caching</li>
            <li>Typed SDKs with observability</li>
            <li>Configurable failure strategies</li>
            <li>Shadow mode for risk-free testing</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="category">
          <div class="category-header">
            <div class="category-icon">üõ°Ô∏è</div>
            <h3>Governance & Trust</h3>
          </div>
          <ul>
            <li>Policy management control plane</li>
            <li>Audit trails and decision traces</li>
            <li>RBAC and approval workflows</li>
            <li>Policy versioning and rollback</li>
            <li>Enterprise deployment options</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Core Capabilities -->
  <section class="capabilities">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Core Capabilities (In Scope)</h2>
      
      <div class="capability-grid">
        <div class="capability-card">
          <div class="capability-number">01</div>
          <h3>Entitlement Decision API</h3>
          <p>Evaluate capability access with deterministic, low-latency responses. Context-aware decisions based on user, organization, and environment.</p>
          <div class="capability-meta">
            <span class="meta-badge">Core</span>
            <span class="meta-tag">Stateless</span>
            <span class="meta-tag">Deterministic</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="capability-card">
          <div class="capability-number">02</div>
          <h3>Policy & Rule Management</h3>
          <p>Define policies declaratively without code changes. Versioned, auditable, and environment-specific policy control.</p>
          <div class="capability-meta">
            <span class="meta-badge">Core</span>
            <span class="meta-tag">Versioned</span>
            <span class="meta-tag">Declarative</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="capability-card">
          <div class="capability-number">03</div>
          <h3>Plan-Capability Mapping</h3>
          <p>Decouple pricing plans from code. Integrate with billing providers as input source only‚Äîwe never process payments.</p>
          <div class="capability-meta">
            <span class="meta-badge">Essential</span>
            <span class="meta-tag">Input-Only</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="capability-card">
          <div class="capability-number">04</div>
          <h3>Trials & Grace Periods</h3>
          <p>Handle trial lifecycles, grace periods, and expiration logic. Emit soft vs hard expiration signals to your application.</p>
          <div class="capability-meta">
            <span class="meta-badge">Essential</span>
            <span class="meta-tag">Time-Aware</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="capability-card">
          <div class="capability-number">05</div>
          <h3>Usage & Limit Evaluation</h3>
          <p>Track usage counters and evaluate limits. Advisory signals only‚Äîenforcement remains in your application.</p>
          <div class="capability-meta">
            <span class="meta-badge">Advisory</span>
            <span class="meta-tag">Non-Blocking</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="capability-card">
          <div class="capability-number">06</div>
          <h3>Snapshots & Caching</h3>
          <p>Precomputed entitlement snapshots for offline-safe behavior. Edge/CDN compatible for global performance.</p>
          <div class="capability-meta">
            <span class="meta-badge">Performance</span>
            <span class="meta-tag">Offline-Safe</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="capability-card">
          <div class="capability-number">07</div>
          <h3>Rollouts & Kill Switches</h3>
          <p>Percentage-based rollouts, segment enablement, and emergency disable capabilities for operational safety.</p>
          <div class="capability-meta">
            <span class="meta-badge">Operational</span>
            <span class="meta-tag">Controlled</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="capability-card">
          <div class="capability-number">08</div>
          <h3>Audit & Decision Trace</h3>
          <p>Complete visibility into why access was allowed or denied. Policy version traceability for compliance and debugging.</p>
          <div class="capability-meta">
            <span class="meta-badge">Compliance</span>
            <span class="meta-tag">Traceable</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Integration Model -->
  <section class="integration-model">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="badge">Architecture</span>
        <h2>How Systems Integrate</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">
          Entitle operates as a consulted system, never an authoritative one. 
          Your application maintains full control over enforcement and data flow.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="integration-steps">
        <div class="integration-step">
          <div class="step-marker">
            <div class="step-icon">üîç</div>
            <div class="step-line"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Call at Decision Boundaries</h3>
            <p>Client systems call Entitle at well-defined decision points only. Never in business logic execution paths.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="integration-step">
          <div class="step-marker">
            <div class="step-icon">üß©</div>
            <div class="step-line"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Anti-Corruption Layer</h3>
            <p>Integration via typed SDKs forms a clean boundary. Your core domain remains protected and independent.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="integration-step">
          <div class="step-marker">
            <div class="step-icon">‚úÖ</div>
            <div class="step-line"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Local Enforcement</h3>
            <p>Your application always enforces decisions. We evaluate policy‚Äîyou control what happens next.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="integration-step">
          <div class="step-marker">
            <div class="step-icon">‚öôÔ∏è</div>
          </div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Configurable Failure Modes</h3>
            <p>Choose fail-open or fail-closed behavior. Snapshots and caching ensure graceful degradation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Non-Functional Requirements -->
  <section class="nfr">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Non-Functional Guarantees</h2>
      <div class="nfr-grid">
        <div class="nfr-card">
          <div class="nfr-icon">‚ö°</div>
          <h3>Performance</h3>
          <p class="nfr-target">P95 &lt; 10ms</p>
          <p class="nfr-desc">Low-latency decision API with cache-first design for production-grade speed.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="nfr-card">
          <div class="nfr-icon">üîí</div>
          <h3>Security</h3>
          <p class="nfr-target">Hard Isolation</p>
          <p class="nfr-desc">Strong tenant isolation with fine-grained RBAC. Row-level security at data layer.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="nfr-card">
          <div class="nfr-icon">üõ°Ô∏è</div>
          <h3>Reliability</h3>
          <p class="nfr-target">Highly Available</p>
          <p class="nfr-desc">Snapshot fallback, explicit staleness rules, and configurable failure strategies.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="nfr-card">
          <div class="nfr-icon">üìä</div>
          <h3>Determinism</h3>
          <p class="nfr-target">100% Reproducible</p>
          <p class="nfr-desc">Same input always produces same output. Testable, auditable, and predictable.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Explicitly Out of Scope -->
  <section class="out-of-scope">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="badge">Clear Boundaries</span>
        <h2>Explicitly Out of Scope</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">
          We believe in architectural discipline. These boundaries are non-negotiable 
          and critical for DDD trust.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="scope-grid">
        <div class="scope-item">
          <div class="scope-icon">‚ùå</div>
          <h3>Business Workflows</h3>
          <p>We don't execute multi-step processes or coordinate business logic. That's your core domain.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="scope-item">
          <div class="scope-icon">‚ùå</div>
          <h3>Feature Behavior Control</h3>
          <p>We don't control what features do‚Äîonly whether access is allowed. Implementation stays in your code.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="scope-item">
          <div class="scope-icon">‚ùå</div>
          <h3>Pricing Strategy</h3>
          <p>We don't optimize pricing or suggest plans. We consume plan data as input, nothing more.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="scope-item">
          <div class="scope-icon">‚ùå</div>
          <h3>Throttling & Blocking</h3>
          <p>We emit signals about limits‚Äîwe don't enforce rate limiting or block requests directly.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="scope-item">
          <div class="scope-icon">‚ùå</div>
          <h3>Billing Systems</h3>
          <p>We integrate with billing providers for input only. We never process payments or manage subscriptions.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="scope-item">
          <div class="scope-icon">‚ùå</div>
          <h3>Product Analytics</h3>
          <p>We don't analyze feature usage outcomes or provide product insights. Decisions only.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="scope-principle">
        <h3>Guiding Principle</h3>
        <p>We sell <strong>capability decisions and trust</strong>, not product behavior. 
        This principle governs all product decisions.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Self-Governing Platform -->
  <section class="self-governing">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="self-gov-content">
        <span class="badge">Dogfooding</span>
        <h2>Self-Governing Platform</h2>
        <p class="intro">
          Entitle uses itself to govern its own access control. The same policy engine, scopes, 
          delegation rules, and approval workflows that customers use are applied internally.
        </p>

        <div class="dogfood-grid">
          <div class="dogfood-item">
            <h4>Entitle as Its Own Tenant</h4>
            <p>We operate as our own tenant within the platform. Internal actions are evaluated through Entitle policies.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="dogfood-item">
            <h4>No Hidden Super-User Logic</h4>
            <p>No hardcoded bypasses or special-case logic. If it exists for us, it exists for you.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="dogfood-item">
            <h4>Production-Grade Discipline</h4>
            <p>Self-dogfooding forces architectural correctness and eliminates operational blind spots.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="enterprise-takeaway">
          <p class="takeaway-quote">
            <strong>Enterprise takeaway:</strong> If Entitle cannot safely govern itself using its own platform, 
            it is not fit to govern yours.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Value to Organizations -->
  <section class="value-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Value to Organizations</h2>
      <div class="value-grid">
        <div class="value-card">
          <div class="value-icon">‚ö°</div>
          <h3>Move Faster</h3>
          <p>Change pricing, plans, or feature access without deployments. Ship commercial changes in minutes, not weeks.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="value-card">
          <div class="value-icon">üîí</div>
          <h3>Reduce Risk</h3>
          <p>Externalize risky entitlement logic from core services. Shadow mode ensures zero-risk adoption.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="value-card">
          <div class="value-icon">üí∞</div>
          <h3>Lower Cost</h3>
          <p>Stop maintaining internal entitlement systems. Predictable subscription replaces ongoing engineering cost.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="value-card">
          <div class="value-icon">üèóÔ∏è</div>
          <h3>Architectural Discipline</h3>
          <p>Clear DDD boundaries prevent entitlement logic from leaking into your core domain.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="value-card">
          <div class="value-icon">üìä</div>
          <h3>Auditability</h3>
          <p>Complete decision traces for compliance. Know exactly why access was granted or denied.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="value-card">
          <div class="value-icon">üîÑ</div>
          <h3>Replaceability</h3>
          <p>No lock-in by design. Clear boundaries mean you can migrate away if needed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Target Users -->
  <section class="target-users">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="users-split">
        <div class="users-column">
          <h2>Who This Is For</h2>
          
          <div class="user-category">
            <h3>Primary Buyers</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>CTOs / Heads of Engineering</li>
              <li>Principal / Staff Engineers</li>
              <li>Platform & Infrastructure teams</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="user-category">
            <h3>Target Companies</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>B2B SaaS (Series A‚ÄìC)</li>
              <li>API-first products</li>
              <li>AI / usage-based SaaS</li>
              <li>Multi-tenant platforms</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="user-category">
            <h3>Use Cases</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Plan-based access control</li>
              <li>Commercial entitlements</li>
              <li>Feature flag proliferation</li>
              <li>Pricing model changes</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="users-column">
          <h2>Not For</h2>
          
          <div class="not-for-list">
            <div class="not-for-item">
              <div class="not-icon">√ó</div>
              <div class="not-content">
                <h4>Consumer Mobile Apps</h4>
                <p>Built for B2B, not consumer-scale mobile applications.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="not-for-item">
              <div class="not-icon">√ó</div>
              <div class="not-content">
                <h4>Early MVP Startups</h4>
                <p>Best for companies with established pricing models and customer segments.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="not-for-item">
              <div class="not-icon">√ó</div>
              <div class="not-content">
                <h4>Feature Flag Experimentation</h4>
                <p>We handle commercial access, not A/B testing or gradual feature rollouts.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Buy vs Build -->
  <section class="buy-vs-build">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why Buy Instead of Build</h2>
      <p class="comparison-intro">
        Enterprises can build similar systems internally. But building requires 
        <strong>permanent ownership</strong> of a complex, cross-cutting domain with high operational risk.
      </p>

      <div class="comparison-table">
        <div class="comparison-row header-row">
          <div class="comparison-cell">Aspect</div>
          <div class="comparison-cell">Build Internally</div>
          <div class="comparison-cell">Use Entitle</div>
        </div>

        <div class="comparison-row">
          <div class="comparison-cell">Initial Cost</div>
          <div class="comparison-cell">6+ months engineering</div>
          <div class="comparison-cell">Integrate in &lt; 1 day</div>
        </div>

        <div class="comparison-row">
          <div class="comparison-cell">Ongoing Cost</div>
          <div class="comparison-cell">Continuous maintenance</div>
          <div class="comparison-cell">Predictable subscription</div>
        </div>

        <div class="comparison-row">
          <div class="comparison-cell">Evolution</div>
          <div class="comparison-cell">Hard to evolve safely</div>
          <div class="comparison-cell">Built to evolve</div>
        </div>

        <div class="comparison-row">
          <div class="comparison-cell">Ownership</div>
          <div class="comparison-cell">Your burden forever</div>
          <div class="comparison-cell">Dedicated ownership</div>
        </div>

        <div class="comparison-row">
          <div class="comparison-cell">Risk</div>
          <div class="comparison-cell">Stays internal</div>
          <div class="comparison-cell">Externalized</div>
        </div>

        <div class="comparison-row">
          <div class="comparison-cell">Architecture</div>
          <div class="comparison-cell">Often leaks boundaries</div>
          <div class="comparison-cell">DDD-aligned by design</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="build-conclusion">
        <p>You <em>can</em> build this. You probably don't want to <strong>own it forever</strong>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="product-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Start Externalizing Entitlement Logic</h2>
      <p>
        Built for enterprise B2B SaaS. Trusted by engineering-led teams who value 
        architectural discipline and production reliability.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-buttons">
        <a href={`${base}alpha`} class="btn btn-primary">Request Alpha Access</a>
        <a href={`${base}docs`} class="btn btn-secondary-light">Read Documentation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Hero Section */
  .product-hero {
    padding: 5rem 0 4rem;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f8fafc 0%, #ffffff 100%);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .product-hero-content {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .product-hero h1 {
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .product-hero .lead {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .product-hero .lead strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  /* Core Value */
  .core-value {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #eff6ff 0%, #dbeafe 100%);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
  }

  .value-statement {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .value-statement h2 {
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-primary-dark);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .value-statement p {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  /* What Delivers */
  .what-delivers {
    padding: 5rem 0;
  }

  .delivery-categories {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(320px, 1fr));
    gap: 2.5rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .category {
    background: white;
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    padding: 2.5rem;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .category:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
    border-color: var(--color-primary-light);
  }

  .category-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .category-icon {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
  }

  .category h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .category ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .category li {
    padding: 0.625rem 0 0.625rem 1.75rem;
    position: relative;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .category li::before {
    content: "‚úì";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-success);
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  /* Capabilities */
  .capabilities {
    padding: 5rem 0;
    background: var(--color-bg-secondary);
  }

  .capabilities h2 {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .capability-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(320px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .capability-card {
    background: white;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    padding: 2rem;
    position: relative;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .capability-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
  }

  .capability-number {
    position: absolute;
    top: 1.5rem;
    right: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.1);
  }

  .capability-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    padding-right: 3rem;
  }

  .capability-card p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .capability-meta {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .meta-badge {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary) 0%, var(--color-primary-dark) 100%);
    color: white;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .meta-tag {
    background: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
